IN THE CIRCUIT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, Norther Division.
In the Matter of the Application of Salfest A. Sylvester for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
No.
MOTION TO QUASH.
Comes now Salfest A. Sylvester the petitioner, by his Solicitor, R. B. Albertson, Esq., and moves the court to quash the return filed herein in response to the Writ of Habeas Corpus issued by this court, on the ground that said return does not show any cause for the imprisonment and detention of said petitioner by the respondents named in said writ, and because it appears therefrom and from all the filed and records herein that said petitioner is entitled to his liberty.
Petitioner further moves the court by reason of the premises, that he be restored to his liberty under said writ of habeas corpus, and that said respondents be restrained and enjoined from holding him any further in custody.
R. B. Albertson Solicitor for said Petitioner
